    "summary": "My name is Luc de Booij owner of PM-Smart B.V. \nSr Program Director, manager and consultant on ICT knowledge area.\nCertified by PMI Project Management Institute as PMP Project Management Professional.\nCertified Agile scrum master, Agile product owner and Professional Agile leader.\n\nRoles : Executive program director/manager, senior project manager, regional project manager, global project lead.\nCurrent role Sr Director Delivery Management at Avanade.\nAssigned as AMD Avanade Managing Director Delivery for the Obvion Account.\nIn addition engaged in continuous Improvement Delivery Community. \nPreviously assigned as Program Delivery Executive on HEINEKEN Global Director Account T-Systems. (5yrs)\nWorked as Program Director assigned to Complex deals for T&T on pe BBC and Province Gelderland.\nNew Complex deals Program Director T&T responsibly. Governmental I&W and Transport Dutch railroads NS.\nProgram Director on the Shell Global Account managing and leading 6 large Storage related programs and 31 projects  in the Storage Overall Program SOP. (4 yrs)\nBenchmark SAP and Dynamic HANA with Shell and ISG Benchmark company (March 2106 \u2013 June 2016) act as SGA focal point.\n\nThe last 25 years assigned to international and national assignments for T-Systems , GXS, DOW, EDS and HP.\nLed different multicultural teams on B2B EDI Managed Services and infrastructure projects in multiple countries and clients in Pacific and Europe.\nGXS completed EDI B2B program on Global account Warner Bros implementing Managed Services in JAPAN and Australia area. Completed MS project for DOLE (Italy, Benelux, Germany), completed 1st phase of a large project for REXEL Nederland.\n\nEmployed by Hewlett-Packard as program manager Business Excellence Program on AHOLD account (2,5 years) scope: infrastructure and deployment. \nAEGON account program manager Service Improvement Program AEGON. Responsible for 20 projects for contract renewal with EDS.\nRegional project manager for EMEA North Region. EDS program internal improvement and financial savings on service desk and 2nd line support.  \nSKF Gothenburg Sweden; on-site project manager NT4 retirement and datacenter consolidation project at head office site SKF Sweden. (1yr)\nGlobal project lead managing and leading infrastructure implementations, datacenter consolidations and builds, different accounts/countries for DOW Chemical.",
